ENTRY            A1095   20260216   20260508   20260508       A132
SUBENT        A1095001   20260216   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                  8         27
TITLE      Polarization and cross section of protons scattered by
           3He from 4 to 13 MeV
AUTHOR     (D.G.Mcdonald,W.Haeberli,L.W.Morrow)
REFERENCE  (J,PR,133,B1178,1964)
INSTITUTE  (1USAWIS)
DETECTOR   (COIN,PROPC,SCIN) Protons scattered symmetrically to
           the right and to the left by the second target were
           counted in two detector telescopes.
SAMPLE     Generally He3 was used as the first target. However,
           for p-He3 measurements at low energies or large
           scattering angles it was advantageous to scatter from
           He4 first so as to have a higher energy in the
           p-alpha scattering and therefore a greater
           polarization. Target pressures in the first target of
           8-20 atm were used. The second target pressure was
           about 6 atm for all measurements. The maximum He3
           target thickness was 180 keV.
REL-REF    (I,,R.I.Brown+,J,NP,47,212,1963) - the apparatus
            was given
HISTORY    (19810421C) This compilation has been produced
           by Arzamas RFNC-VNIIEF
           (20040630A) Ref. was corrected. Updated to new date
           formats, lower case.
           (20081015A) NDS: ref. was corrected.
                          PR,B133,1178 ==>PR,133,B1178
           (20260216U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           EN-ERR1 -> EN-ERR; ANG2-ERR -> ANG-ERR.
ENDBIB              27
COMMON               2          3
EN-ERR     ANG-ERR
MEV        ADEG
      0.015        0.2
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           34
SUBENT        A1095002   20260216   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                  5          7
REACTION   (2-HE-3(P,EL)2-HE-3,,DA)
DETECTOR   (SIBAR)
STATUS     (TABLE,,D.G.Mcdonald+,J,PR,133,B1178,1964) Table II
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) The over-all estimated uncertainty of the
           cross section. (Both systematic and random).
           (ERR-S,,1.) Statistical error
HISTORY    (20260216A) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB               7
